{"id":"2544730189","type":"page","ari":"ari:cloud:confluence:4e3a1a04-13f1-4674-95f6-44812aec1da3:page/2544730189","base64EncodedAri":"YXJpOmNsb3VkOmNvbmZsdWVuY2U6NGUzYTFhMDQtMTNmMS00Njc0LTk1ZjYtNDQ4MTJhZWMxZGEzOmNvbnRlbnQvMjU0NDczMDE4OQ==","status":"archived","title":"VPN Configuration (DEPRECATED)","version":{"by":{"type":"known","accountId":"5f3d2a10ea5e2f003979db69","accountType":"atlassian","email":"","publicName":"Ignacio Jorge","profilePicture":{"path":"/wiki/aa-avatar/5f3d2a10ea5e2f003979db69","width":48,"height":48,"isDefault":false},"displayName":"Ignacio Jorge","isExternalCollaborator":false,"isGuest":false,"locale":"en_US","accountStatus":"active","_expandable":{"operations":"","personalSpace":""},"_links":{"self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/user?accountId=5f3d2a10ea5e2f003979db69"}},"when":"2025-01-21T21:26:21.157Z","friendlyWhen":"Jan 21, 2025","message":"","number":13,"minorEdit":false,"syncRev":"3.confluence$content$2544730189.37","syncRevSource":"synchrony-ack","ncsStepVersion":"18","ncsStepVersionSource":"ncs-ack","confRev":"confluence$content$2544730189.67","contentTypeModified":false,"_expandable":{"collaborators":"","content":"/rest/api/content/2544730189?status=archived"},"_links":{"self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/2544730189/version/13"}},"ancestors":[],"macroRenderedOutput":{},"body":{"storage":{"value":"<p>This document will explain how to configure the native MacOS VPN to have access to Bancard services and servers.</p><p /><p><strong>Table of Contents</strong></p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"toc\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" data-layout=\"default\" ac:local-id=\"5be2fbf4-8199-4a17-b24a-83dcd5ceb77d\" ac:macro-id=\"c6a8ff52a512ce8bb55389bebdfb3c77\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"minLevel\">1</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name=\"maxLevel\">7</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro><h2>Prerequisites</h2><ul><li><p>VPN user (ask the tech lead or team lead)</p></li><li><p>Shared Secret: <code>mooveit2023</code></p></li></ul><h2>Steps for MacOS Monterey</h2><ol start=\"1\"><li><p>Go to the Mac System Preferences:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"324\" ac:original-width=\"277\" ac:width=\"204\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230309-203233.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Go to the Network section:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"216\" ac:original-width=\"671\" ac:width=\"476\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"Screen Shot 2023-03-09 at 17.34.12-20230309-203508.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"2\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Create a new service:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"524\" ac:original-width=\"210\" ac:width=\"136\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"Screen Shot 2023-03-09 at 17.36.48-20230309-203708.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"4\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Configure the interface, VPN type and Service Name as follows:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"192\" ac:original-width=\"417\" ac:width=\"306\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230309-203919.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p><strong>Interface:</strong> VPN<br /><strong>VPN Type:</strong> Cisco IPSec<br /><strong>Service Name:</strong> Bancard VPN (IPSec)<br />You can choose the service name, this is just a suggestion.<br /></p></li><li><p>Configure the VPN:<br />For this step, you will need a VPN user. Ask the tech lead or team lead for one.</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"455\" ac:original-width=\"448\" ac:width=\"306\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230309-204853.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p><strong>Server Address:</strong> 201.217.159.98<br /><strong>Account Name:</strong> &lt;VPN user&gt;<br /><strong>Password:[PASSWORD] &lt;VPN user password&gt;<br /></p></li><li><p>Go to Authentication Settings:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"467\" ac:original-width=\"461\" ac:width=\"306\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"Screen Shot 2023-03-09 at 17.52.07-20230309-205232.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Configure the machine authentication:<br />For this step, you will need the Shared Secret. Ask the tech lead or team lead.</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"195\" ac:original-width=\"369\" ac:width=\"306\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230309-205343.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p><strong>Shared Secret:</strong> &lt;Shared Secret&gt;<br /><strong>Group Name:</strong> group5<br /></p></li><li><p>Ensure to enable the option to show VPN status in the menu bar:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"466\" ac:original-width=\"459\" ac:width=\"306\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"Screen Shot 2023-03-09 at 18.02.58-20230309-210324.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Apply the changes.</p></li><li><p>Now, you will be able to connect to the VPN from the menu bar as shown in the following image:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"209\" ac:original-width=\"346\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230309-210631.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image></li></ol><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MISSION ACCOMPLISHED! </strong><ac:emoticon ac:name=\"blue-star\" ac:emoji-shortname=\":white_check_mark:\" ac:emoji-id=\"2705\" ac:emoji-fallback=\"✅\" /></p><p /><h2>Steps for MacOS Ventura</h2><ol start=\"1\"><li><p>Go to the Mac System Preferences:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"317\" ac:original-width=\"274\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230421-194826.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Go to the Network section:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"384\" ac:original-width=\"218\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230421-194940.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Add a new VPN configuration, remember to select the Cisco IPSec option:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"629\" ac:original-width=\"995\" ac:width=\"646\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230421-195550.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Configure the VPN, including the authentication:<br />For this step, you will need a VPN user and the shared secret. Ask the tech lead or team lead.</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"199\" ac:original-width=\"432\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230421-200149.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"159\" ac:original-width=\"431\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230421-200228.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p><strong>Display Name:</strong> Bancard VPN (IPSec)<br />You can choose the service name, this is just a suggestion.<br /><strong>Server address:</strong> 201.217.159.98<br /><strong>Account Name:</strong> &lt;VPN user&gt;<br /><strong>Password[PASSWORD]> &lt;VPN user password&gt;<br /><strong>Authentication Type:</strong> Shared Secret<br /><strong>Authentication Shared Secret:</strong> &lt;Shared Secret&gt;<br /><strong>Authentication Group Name: </strong>group5<br /></p></li><li><p>Ensure to enable the option to show VPN status in the menu bar:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"621\" ac:original-width=\"708\" ac:width=\"408\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"Screenshot 2023-04-21 at 17.28.03-20230421-202901.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></li><li><p>Now, you will be able to connect to the VPN from the menu bar as shown in the following image:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"203\" ac:original-width=\"288\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20230421-203506.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image></li></ol><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MISSION ACCOMPLISHED!  </strong><ac:emoticon ac:name=\"blue-star\" ac:emoji-shortname=\":white_check_mark:\" ac:emoji-id=\"2705\" ac:emoji-fallback=\"✅\" /><strong> </strong></p><p />","representation":"storage","embeddedContent":[],"_expandable":{"content":"/rest/api/content/2544730189?status=archived"}},"_expandable":{"editor":"","atlas_doc_format":"","view":"","export_view":"","styled_view":"","dynamic":"","editor2":"","anonymous_export_view":""}},"extensions":{"position":1810},"_expandable":{"childTypes":"","container":"/rest/api/space/BAN","schedulePublishInfo":"","metadata":"","operations":"","schedulePublishDate":"","children":"/rest/api/content/2544730189/child","restrictions":"/rest/api/content/2544730189/restriction/byOperation","history":"/rest/api/content/2544730189/history","draftVersion":"","descendants":"/rest/api/content/2544730189/descendant","space":"/rest/api/space/BAN"},"_links":{"editui":"/pages/resumedraft.action?draftId=2544730189","webui":"/spaces/BAN/pages/2544730189/VPN+Configuration+DEPRECATED","edituiv2":"/spaces/BAN/pages/edit-v2/2544730189","context":"/wiki","self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/2544730189?status=archived","tinyui":"/x/TYCtlw","collection":"/rest/api/content","base":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki"}}